{
  "text": "Some calculations have estimated that the muon flux from gamma ray sources could be sufficient for neutrino telescopes to detect them. However, most attempts to estimate this muon flux rely on one-dimensional analytic models, and do not take into account the muon propagation from sea level to the detector and the detector sensitivity. A first attempt to estimate the underwater flux using a MONTE CARLO simulation, without considering detection efficiency, has found gamma ray sources to be hardly detectable by a neutrino telescope [CITATION_1] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
